getting ready for a show i'm getting ready for the opening night of a musical i'm in tonight i was just wondering if anyone had tips or ideas to get me ready what to eat to save energy what to sing to warm up what to do when i get nervous anything really thanks lots and lots of water i can stress this enough staying hydrated will not only make you feel better overall but it will also help by keeping your voice in line as well as for energy try to eat something that is low in fat but high in carbs maybe even a power bar or two then about thirty minutes before you go on just find a place to relax and center yourself it's often overlooked as an element but relaxation and breathing can help you in ways you never thought hope the performance is a success break a leg Jon Secada Anorexia nervosa The Ashlee Simpson Show Bong The Emancipation of Mimi Insomnia Aikido Avenue Q Carburetor Louis Armstrong Rent (musical) Weight training Rod Stewart Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Low-carbohydrate diet Quarashi Atkins Nutritional Approach Garth Brooks Social rule Water (molecule) Socrate The Shining (film) Futurama (TV series - season 2) Insulin Mercury Atlas 6 Conspiracy (TNG episode) Nashville Skyline Fasting South Beach diet Meat Loaf The Jazz Singer Carbohydrate Equine conformation We Belong Together Marching band Breaststroke Coconut crab Restaurant Oh My Goddess! Diving Decompression sickness Swimming Ecology Genesis (band) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Drowning Stuttering Thermoregulation Hydrogen sulfide Carbon dioxide Sleep Salad Fingers Ceramics Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Street-Legal Shaggy dog story Terri Schiavo Hypoglycemia The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie The Amazing Race Meditation Solar power Portland cement Veganism Marathon (sport) Current teachings of Prem Rawat Characters in the Smurfs Urinary incontinence Premature ejaculation Aerial (dance move) Blood on the Tracks Tony Bennett Tae eul ju Toyota Prius Internal ballistics Egg (food) Reiki No